{"questionId":"1251248","questionHtml":"<p>A sample of a pure radioactive nuclide initially contains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math> atoms. The initial activity of the&nbsp;sample is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>A second sample of the same nuclide initially contains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>N</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math> atoms.</p>\n<p>What is the activity of the second sample after three half lives?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"1251248","referenceCode":"21M.1A.HL.TZ2.20","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A sample of a pure radioactive nuclide initially contains N0 atoms. The initial activity of the sample is A0. A second sample of the same nuclide initially contains 2N0 atoms. What","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"20","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["E. Nuclear and quantum physics","E.3 Radioactive decay"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}